Too many things about her appearance point in one specific direction.

Missy is one of a nonhuman species that never evolved in our world. The timeline where her species originated diverged from ours some time during the Miocene, one in which primates never appeared. Its intelligent, sapient, apex predator species is a mammal of a clade never appearing in our world. They are of Order Carnivora, Suborder Fissipeda, of a clade that appeared on Madagascar 50-60 million years ago, starting out in the evolutionary niche that lemurs occupied in our timeline. That's why she's so slender, and why her arms are so long. It's why her hands are shaped the way they are, and why she has claws. It's also why she has a hyperactive metabolism and an uncommon taste for sweets. She's built for brachiation in a tropical hardwood forest.

Her ancestors won out in competition with other pseudo-lemur carnivores three or four million years back, broadened their diet with insectivory as a supplemental source of high-quality protein, then true omnivory, and figured out fire about a hundred thousand to a hundred and fifty thousand years ago. Around seventy-five thousand years ago they began building rafts and colonized the African mainland, then Europe, Asia, Australia, and the Americas. Their technology in Current Year is grossly similar to our own. They didn't send an infant here. How Missy got here is very Missyterious. Maybe aliens were involved.
